DataElement.preferredDefinition: Sequence; serial arrangement in which things follow in logical order or a recurrent pattern._The worldwide standard for the code numbers used by computers to represent all the uppercase and lowercase Latin letters, numbers, punctuation, and other symbols. There are 128 standard ASCII codes, each of which can be represented by a 7 digit binary number: 0000000 through 1111111.:An expression consisting of a linear sequence of symbols (characters or words or phrases)._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
